steps.instruction:
- Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of plastic wrap and pound with a mallet until they are an even 1/2 inch
- Sift together flour, salt, black pepper, ground ginger, nutmeg, thyme, sage, paprika, and cayenne pepper
    - This amount of spices is actually good for 2 batches, save it or grab 4 more  breasts
- Make an egg wash by beating water and eggs together
- Season the chicken breasts with salt and pepper
- Cover them in the flour and spice mixture
- Heat a skillet with about a 1/2 inch of canola oil on medium heat
- Fry for about 4 to 5 minutes per side
- Drain on wire rack
- In a saucepan add the olive oil and minced garlic and cook on medium heat will the garlic softens
- Add honey, soy sauce, and black pepper
- Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes
- Cover the fried breasts in the honey sauce
